<section class="why">
  <p>
    Flue feels like Claude Code, but you drive it. Same building blocks (sessions, skills,
    sandboxes, tool calls), wrapped in a function you write. Each agent compiles to a Worker.
    Sessions get a Durable Object for free, R2 can be the agent's filesystem, and the same
    agent code runs on Workers, Node, or any CI. Everything below deploys to Workers via
    <a href="https://alchemy.run">alchemy</a>, no wrangler config.
  </p>
</section>

